HEADWORD: Rawly
<hw>Raw"ly</hw>, <pos>adv.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>In a raw manner;
unskillfully; without experience.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Without proper preparation or provision.</def>
<rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Rawness</ent>⟦br⟧
